# Relative astrometry of KELT-4B with respect to KELT-4C.
# Wired into kelt4.yaml as astrometryinstrument 'BC' (mode: rel,
# orbit: BC, sep_unit: mas): the model is the companion group (B)
# relative to the primary group (C).
#
# Columns: time[BJD_TDB]  sep[mas]  err_sep[mas]  pa[deg]  err_pa[deg]
#
# pa is the position angle East of North (per astrometryinstrument convention).
# time = J2000.0 + (decimal_year - 2000.0) * 365.25 (Julian-year epoch -> JD;
# TT/TDB distinction is negligible at this precision).
#
# Only one epoch resolves B from C individually (2012.3464, high-resolution
# AO); earlier epochs in the source table only resolved A from the BC
# photocenter (see KELT-4_A-BC.rel.dat) -- a single epoch constrains the
# B-C separation/PA at that time but not their relative orbital motion.
#
# epoch      time[BJD_TDB]  sep     err_sep  pa       err_pa   source
2456054.523      49.14   0.39     325.230   0.13   # 2012.3464 source 5
